Today i learnt how to investigate suspicious powershell activity from a soc analyst perceptive 

## scenario
the commands were ran on FINANCE-LAPTOP-03:

"powershell.exe  -ExecutionPolicy Bypass - NoProfile -WindowStyle Hidden"

Addition activities: 

- powershell launched from a word document 
- connected to an external ip address
- downloaded a file into AppData
- created a scheduled task

## New concept: Persistance 
this is a method  that lets suspicious activity carry-on or restart even after the user logs out or the computer restarts 


## ## Suspicious Indicators
- PowerShell was launched from a Word document.
- The command used ExecutionPolicy Bypass.
- The command used WindowStyle Hidden.
- The device connected to an external IP address.
- A file was downloaded into AppData.
- A scheduled task was created, which may indicate persistence.

## Evidence Still Needed
- Check the reputation of the external IP address.
- Inspect the downloaded file.
- Review the scheduled task details.
- Check process logs.
- Investigate how the Word document arrived on the device.
- Check whether other devices ran the same command.

## Risk Level
High

## Recommended Actions
- Investigate the external IP address.
- Analyse the downloaded file.
- Review and remove the scheduled task if confirmed malicious.
- Isolate the device if malicious activity is suspected.
- Check other devices for similar PowerShell activity.
